<item>
            <title>[LU-15697] sanity-lnet test_211: Expect 0 NIDs found: peer NI recovery:</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15697</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/b829f9da-7d3b-4c1a-b543-666b4523b04a&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/b829f9da-7d3b-4c1a-b543-666b4523b04a&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test_211 failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;$&apos;Expect 0 NIDs found: peer NI recovery:n    nid-0: 10.240.44.204@tcp&apos;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Have seen this &lt;b&gt;very&lt;/b&gt; intermittently, only 4 times in the past 9 months.  Probably due to a slowdown in VMs during testing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Likely improved by sleeping more than 7s in the test, preferably with &lt;tt&gt;wait_update()&lt;/tt&gt; so that it only waits the minimum amount of time needed.  &lt;tt&gt;wait_update()&lt;/tt&gt; can also be used in other parts of the test instead of sleeping a fixed amount of time.&lt;/p&gt;





&lt;p&gt;VVVVVVV DO NOT REMOVE LINES BELOW, Added by Maloo for auto-association VVVVVVV&lt;br/&gt;
sanity-lnet test_211 - Expect 0 NIDs found: peer NI recovery:n    nid-0:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
